snippet.textDisplay:
To everyone surprised by the emotional reaction of the houseguests:

You have had the privilege of experiencing the gradual changes of the world caused by COVID-19 (and measures to combat it) on a daily basis. You are not secluded from the outside world, even in quarantine. These people have entered a show focused on isolation and were expecting to see it through til the end. All they know about the pandemic is the short messages by Erin. They don’t know what the world looks like, all they know is that everything has shut down. To us, the situation is scary enough as is. For people who don’t have daily access to media, news broadcasts and who are literally escaping reality, this sounds like the actual end of the world. Imagine them having to come back to a world they don’t know. They’ll be confused as to why no one is shaking hands, why the media is focused on social distancing. You know this and are somewhat used to it because you’ve experienced every step of the process. They will be thrown headfirst into a world that has shut down. This is like Rick Grimes waking up in the middle of a zombie apocalypse. We know it’s not THAT bad, but they don’t. This. Is. Fucking. Horrifying.
